1.14.24  4:24 pm   hi bill, i'm a classical ballet dancer. it's audition season right now, and i'm super nervous. any tips for getting the physical side of nervousness (i.e. shaky muscles, racing heart, etc) to go away? thanks

      do more auditions. the bad news is, i think nothing else really cures it. the good news is, doing that definitely cures it

1.14.24  3:53 pm   Is it possible to recreate something without ever having done it, only going off of how other people described it to me?

1.14.24  3:47 pm   If the laws of physics always and always had remained the same, does that mean ever since the start of the universe everything was just following certain set of rules?

     sure but as part of those rules, the rules have changed, according to the rules of change, etc. especially near the 'beginning' of the universe maybe

      Does that mean everything that has happened in the world was guaranteed to happen? I might be overthinking this.

     everything happens eventually somewhere/sometime. but there are infinite different possibilities of how that may unfold
